com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.jdbc

Class DefaultJdbcApplicationReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.configuration.AbstractConfigurable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.server.component.ComponentHelper
        • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.jdbc.JdbcPeerApplicationBase
          • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.jdbc.DefaultJdbcApplicationReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPeerApplicationReader, IPeerApplicationResultSet, IComponent, IHasAttributes, IConfigurable, IRegisterable

    public class DefaultJdbcApplicationReader
extends JdbcPeerApplicationBase
implements IPeerApplicationReader, IPeerApplicationResultSet
    Default JDBC implementation of the IPeerApplicationReader interface.

    This class manages a single JDBC connection and supports a number of configurable prepared statements, which may either be SQL or stored procedure names, as follows:

    • A prepared statement for polling the database for rows of data to send to FIX. Such rows are expected to contain the special house-keeping columns COL_MSG_ID and COL_STATUS. This statement is expected to be parameterless and backs the implementation of read().
    • A prepared statement for updating the COL_STATUS column of a given row. This statement expects two integer parameters (status, nextMsgId) and backs the implementations markAsRead(), markAsSent() and markAsError(java.lang.Object).
    • A prepared statement for determining the maximum COL_MSG_ID of all messages which are not to be sent (i.e. all messages which have either been sent or marked as erroneous).

    Statements which are configured as stored procedure names must also be configured with the corresponding stored procedure flag switched on.
